---
import StaticArticlePage from '@/components/ui/StaticArticlePage.astro'
import { getLegalContactLinks } from '@/lib/legal-contact'
import { getPrivacyHref } from '@/lib/privacy-links'

const { legalEmail, supportEmail } = getLegalContactLinks()
const privacyContactEmail = legalEmail ?? supportEmail
---

<StaticArticlePage
  description="How SeniorPath collects, uses, shares, and protects personal data."
  englishHref={getPrivacyHref('en')}
  kicker="Legal"
  portugueseHref={getPrivacyHref('pt-br')}
  title="Privacy Policy"
>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how SeniorPath and related services operated by Fengsoft collect,
    use, share, and protect personal data. Some features described here may not be available at all
    times. This policy applies when you browse SeniorPath, subscribe to updates, contact us, create
    an account, join challenges, purchase products, or interact with related tools, offers, and
    services connected to SeniorPath.
  </p>

  <h2>Who controls your data</h2>
  <p>
    SeniorPath is operated by FENGSOFT SERVICOS EM TECNOLOGIA E EDUCACAO LTDA, CNPJ
    43.257.394/0001-70, based in Niteroi, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil.
    {privacyContactEmail ? (
      <>
        {' '}
        For privacy questions or requests about your personal data, contact us at{' '}
        <a href={privacyContactEmail.href}>{privacyContactEmail.value}</a>.
      </>
    ) : null}
  </p>

  <h2>What we collect</h2>
  <p>Depending on how you use SeniorPath, we may collect:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Information you provide directly, such as your name, email address, profile details, contact
      messages, challenge submissions, waitlist details, support requests, or other information you
      choose to send us
    </li>
    <li>
      Account and authentication data, such as login identifiers, account status, authentication
      provider details, session records, and security-related information
    </li>
    <li>
      Usage data, such as pages viewed, routes visited, clicks, interactions, timestamps, referrers,
      and general navigation patterns
    </li>
    <li>
      Technical data, such as IP address, browser type, device information, operating system, and
      similar online identifiers
    </li>
    <li>
      Preference and product-state data stored in your browser or account, such as locale, saved UI
      state, progress markers, challenge progress, and similar settings
    </li>
    <li>
      Data we receive from providers or integrations you choose to use, such as authentication,
      payments, newsletters, comments, analytics, advertising, or support tools
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How we use personal data</h2>
  <p>We may use personal data to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Provide, operate, maintain, and improve SeniorPath and related services</li>
    <li>Remember preferences and keep the site and account features working correctly</li>
    <li>
      Measure traffic, understand what content is useful, and improve navigation, editorial quality,
      and product decisions
    </li>
    <li>
      Enable accounts, login flows, challenges, progress tracking, downloads, subscriptions, or paid
      features when available
    </li>
    <li>Send newsletters, service messages, updates, launch announcements, and other communications</li>
    <li>
      Recommend relevant content, products, services, or promotions from SeniorPath, Fengsoft, Capta,
      and related projects
    </li>
    <li>
      Measure campaigns, personalize promotions, and, where enabled, support advertising or sponsored
      placements
    </li>
    <li>Detect abuse, prevent fraud, enforce our terms, and protect users, our rights, and our services</li>
    <li>Comply with legal, regulatory, tax, accounting, or dispute-related obligations</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Legal bases for processing</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on the context, we may rely on one or more legal bases under applicable law, including
    consent, performance of a contract or steps related to a contract, compliance with legal or
    regulatory obligations, regular exercise of rights, and our legitimate interests in operating,
    securing, improving, and growing SeniorPath in a way that does not override your rights and
    freedoms.
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies, browser storage, analytics, and similar technologies</h2>
  <p>
    SeniorPath may use cookies, local storage, pixels, SDKs, and similar technologies to keep the
    site working, remember preferences, support login flows, measure traffic and performance, and,
    where enabled, personalize promotions or advertising.
  </p>
  <p>Depending on the feature, these technologies may fall into categories such as:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Strictly necessary, such as security, session handling, login, and core site functionality</li>
    <li>Preferences, such as locale, saved settings, and product state</li>
    <li>
      Analytics, such as pageviews, navigation paths, campaign attribution, and product usage
      measurement
    </li>
    <li>Marketing, such as promotion measurement, audience segmentation, and advertising-related tracking</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Where required, we will ask for consent before using non-essential cookies or similar
    technologies. You can refuse or manage those categories through our consent controls and can
    change your choices later.
  </p>
  <p>
    Refusing non-essential cookies should not prevent access to the main public parts of the site,
    although some optional features may work differently.
  </p>
  <p>
    If account features are enabled and you are logged in, we may associate certain usage events
    with your account to save progress, improve the product, understand usage patterns, and
    recommend more relevant content or offers.
  </p>

  <h2>Newsletters, product updates, and marketing</h2>
  <p>
    If you subscribe or otherwise interact with us, we may send editorial updates, product
    announcements, launch news, service messages, and promotional communications about SeniorPath,
    Capta, Fengsoft services, and related products.
  </p>
  <p>
    You can unsubscribe from non-essential marketing emails at any time through the unsubscribe link
    in the email or by contacting us.
  </p>
  <p>
    We may use information about your interactions with SeniorPath, such as pages visited, challenge
    activity, or previous signups, to better understand interest in related Fengsoft products and to
    show more relevant internal promotions, recommendations, or launch communications.
  </p>

  <h2>How we share personal data</h2>
  <p>We may share personal data with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Hosting, CDN, infrastructure, security, analytics, and observability providers</li>
    <li>
      Authentication, email, newsletter, payment, advertising, customer support, and comment or
      community providers
    </li>
    <li>Professional advisors, auditors, or legal authorities when reasonably necessary</li>
    <li>Business counterparties involved in a merger, acquisition, reorganization, financing, or asset sale</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do not sell your personal data.</p>
  <p>
    When service providers process data on our behalf, we expect them to do so only for the
    contracted purposes and with appropriate safeguards.
  </p>

  <h2>International transfers</h2>
  <p>
    Some of our providers may store or process personal data outside Brazil. When that happens, we
    will use the applicable legal mechanisms and safeguards required for international data
    transfers.
  </p>

  <h2>How long we keep data</h2>
  <p>
    We keep personal data only for as long as needed for the purposes described in this policy,
    including to provide the service, maintain records, comply with legal obligations, resolve
    disputes, enforce agreements, and protect the platform.
  </p>
  <p>
    Retention periods may vary by feature. For example, newsletter data may be kept until you
    unsubscribe, account data may be kept while your account remains active, and some logs or backup
    records may be retained for security, fraud-prevention, legal, or operational reasons. We may
    keep aggregated or anonymized data for longer.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>
    We use reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect personal data against
    unauthorized access, loss, misuse, alteration, or disclosure. No method of storage or
    transmission is completely secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    Subject to applicable law, you may have the right to request confirmation of processing, access,
    correction, anonymization, blocking or deletion of data, portability, information about sharing,
    information about consent and its consequences, revocation of consent, opposition to certain
    processing, and review of decisions based solely on automated processing where applicable.
  </p>
  {privacyContactEmail ? (
    <p>
      To exercise your rights, contact us at{' '}
      <a href={privacyContactEmail.href}>{privacyContactEmail.value}</a>. We may request information
      reasonably necessary to verify your identity and process the request.
    </p>
  ) : null}

  <h2>Third-party services and external links</h2>
  <p>
    SeniorPath may use or link to third-party services such as analytics tools, newsletter
    platforms, authentication providers, payment processors, GitHub, Giscus, embedded media, or
    external websites. Those services operate under their own terms and privacy policies, and we are
    not responsible for their independent practices.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in the product, legal
    requirements, providers, or data practices. The latest version will always be published on this
    page with its effective date.
  </p>

  {privacyContactEmail ? (
    <>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this policy or about how your personal data is handled, contact{' '}
        <a href={privacyContactEmail.href}>{privacyContactEmail.value}</a>.
      </p>
    </>
  ) : null}
</StaticArticlePage>
